## 📥 How to Install

1. Download the latest `.exe` from the **Releases** page of this repo.  
2. Run the `.exe` and complete the installation (or open it if it is portable).  
3. Open **AI Message Responder**.

---

## 🔑 Choose AI model & add API key

1. In the app, select your **AI model**: `Gemini / Groq / SambaNova / OpenRouter`.  
2. Paste your **API key** for the chosen provider.

> Gemini and Groq are recommended for best performance and speed.

Where to get API keys:

- **Gemini** (Google):  
  Go to Google AI Studio → API Keys:  
  https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey[web:28][web:29]

- **Groq**:  
  Sign in to the Groq Console and create an API key:  
  https://console.groq.com/[web:33][web:37]

- **SambaNova**:  
  Create an account and generate an API key on the SambaNova API keys page:  
  https://cloud.sambanova.ai/ or via their quickstart docs:  
  https://docs.sambanova.ai/docs/en/get-started/quickstart[web:34]

- **OpenRouter**:  
  Log in to OpenRouter and create an API key:  
  https://openrouter.ai/keys[web:35]

Copy your key from each site and paste it into the app’s API key field.  
Keep your keys **secret** and do not share them publicly.

---

## 🖼️ Select chat and input areas

1. Open the chat app you want to automate (WhatsApp, Discord, etc.) and make sure the chat is visible.  
2. In AI Message Responder, click the button **“Select region”** and drag over the **chat messages area**.  
3. Click the button below (for input) and drag over the **typing/input area** where the AI should type.  
4. Save or confirm the selection in the app.

---

## ▶️ Start the bot

1. Set your **bot personality** (optional but recommended).  
2. Click **Start** / **Run** in the app.  
3. The app will now:
   - Watch the selected chat region,
   - Read new messages,
   - Send them to the chosen AI model,
   - Type the reply into the input area and send it automatically.

You can stop it anytime using the **Stop** button or by closing the app.
